.TH "e1000e_disable_aspm" 9 "e1000e_disable_aspm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
e1000e_disable_aspm \- Disable ASPM states.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" e1000e_disable_aspm
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "u16 state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
pointer to PCI device struct
.IP "state" 12
bit-mask of ASPM states to disable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function acquires the pci_bus_sem!
Some devices *must* have certain ASPM states disabled per hardware errata.
